      "description": "Pebble estimate of outstanding compaction work per node, summed across all raft groups on that node, in bytes. `sum by (node_id)` — not `max` — because each group keeps its own compaction queue and real node-level backlog is the sum; `max` would drop all but the busiest group and under-report compaction pressure on nodes hosting more than one group. Growing unboundedly means compaction is losing the race. Thresholds: green <100 MiB, yellow 100-500 MiB, red >=500 MiB. Upper bound is context-dependent so no stall-line is drawn on the trend.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
